    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-31T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-31T11:00:00-05:00" n="439"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.49 Refugees/2397: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Trujillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-31T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 31, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 31—12:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. From Pell. The meeting<note n="4" xml:id="d439fn4">The meeting was held
                        January 30 through February 3, 1941; <hi rend="italic">Report on the Meeting
                            of the Intergovernmental Committee at Ciudad Trujillo and the Sosua
                            Settlement in the Dominican Republic</hi>, dated February 28, 1941.
                        (840.48 Refugees/2585).</note> took place without incident after Barois
                    agreed to hand a memorandum of the plan described in Legation’s telegram No. 18,
                    January 29, 1 p.m., to the Secretary of the Intergovernmental Committee<note
                        n="5" xml:id="d439fn5">Alfred Wagg.</note> for reference as to distribution
                    to the Chairman.<note n="6" xml:id="d439fn6">The Earl of Winterton.</note>
                    [Pell.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
